{
  "text": "We first aimed to validate our rare variant burden test by performing it on all AD cases (n 5 2161) and all AD controls (n 5 3657). When we did this, we found our top hit to be SORL1 and our third top hit to be ABCA7 ( Fig. 4 , Supplementary Table 9 ). This finding confirmed the validity of our method because both SORL1 and ABCA7 are wellknown AD risk loci [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Interestingly, our macaque neuronal gene expression data also identified SORL1 to be highly regulated by estrogen ( Fig. 2 , Supplementary  Table 1 ).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "11341792",
